  {
    "index": 64,
    "texts": [
      "PSC WIDER CONCRETE",
      "SLEEPER T8746",
      "(FOR 60KG RAILS)",
      "A prestressed concrete sleeper built",
      "to RDSO’s T8746 standard, tailored",
      "for loop line installation where rail seat",
      "spacing varies from 103mm to 151mm.",
      "Compatible with 60Kg rails, this sleeper",
      "includes elastic rail clips (ERCs), GFN",
      "liners, And GRSP pads, designed for",
      "heavy axle loads up to 25t."
    ],
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "index": 65,
    "texts": [
      "Galvanized H-beam sleepers are",
      "high-strength steel railway supports",
      "fabricated from single rolled H-beam",
      "sections (commonly ISHB-200),",
      "hot-dip galvanized to prevent corrosion.",
      "They act as robust, durable foundations",
      "for railway tracks, particularly on steel",
      "Girder bridges where traditional ballast",
      "cannot be used.",
      "GALVANIZED",
      "H-BEAM SLEEPERS"
    ],
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "index": 66,
    "texts": [
      "Crossing sleepers (also known as crossing timbers or turnouts)",
      "are specialized, long-length sleepers used in railway",
      "engineering to support the complex geometry of points and",
      "crossings, where one track diverges from another. Unlike",
      "standard sleepers that are of uniform length and placed",
      "perpendicular to the rail, crossing sleepers are designed to",
      "accommodate the converging or diverging rails at a turnout",
      "CROSSING",
      "SLEEPERS"
    ],
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "index": 67,
    "texts": [
      "TRACK MACHINES"
